[5] Polio eradication initiative global update as of 12 Dec 2012
Date: 12 Dec 2012
Source: Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx


Global Polio Eradication Initiative update as of 12 Dec 2012
------------------------------------------------------------
Total cases
Year-to-date 2012 / Year-to-date 2011 / Total in 2011*
Globally: 213 / 571 / 650
- in endemic countries: 208 / 281 / 341
- in non-endemic countries: 5 / 290 / 309

Case breakdown by country
Country: Year-to-date 2012 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Year-to-date 2011 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Total in 2011* / Date of most recent case
Pakistan: 53 / 2 / 1 / 56 // 171 / 2 / 0 / 161 // 198 / 10 Nov 2012
Afghanistan: 34 / 0 / 0 / 34 // 61 / 0 / 0 / 61 // 80 / 19 Nov 2012
Nigeria: 98 / 20 / 0 / 118 // 36 / 10 / 0 / 46 // 62 / 17 Nov 2012
India: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 1 / 13 Jan 2011
Chad: 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 114 / 3 / 0 / 117 // 132 / 14 Jun 2012
DR Congo: 0 / 0/ 0 / 0 // 88 / 0 / 0 / 88 // 93 / 20 Dec 2011
Angola: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 5 / 7 Jul 2011
Niger: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 1 / 0 / 3 // 5 / 22 Dec 2011
CAR: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 2 / 0 / 0 / 2 // 4 / 8 Dec 2011
China: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 18 / 0 / 0 / 18 // 21 / 9 Oct 2011
Guinea: 0 / 0/ 0 / 0 // 0 / 3 / 0 / 3 // 3 / 3 Aug 2011
Kenya: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 1 / 30 Jul 2011
Cote d'Ivoire: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 0 / 36 / 0 / 36 // 36 / 24 Jul 2011
Mali: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 0 / 7 / 0 / 7 // 7 / 23 Jun 2011
Congo: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 1 / 22 Jan 2011
Gabon: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 1 / 15 Jan 2011
Total: 190 / 22 / 1 / 213 // 508 / 63 / 0 / 571 // 650
Total in endemic countries: 185 / 22 / 1 / 208 // 269 / 12 / 0 / 281 // 341
Total outbreak: 5 / 0 / 0 / 5 // 239 / 51 / 0 / 290 // 309

*Data in WHO as of 13 Dec 2011 for 2011 data and 11 Dec 2012 for 2012 data

Two polio vaccinators were killed in Afghanistan last week [week ending 5 Dec 2012] in separate incidents, underlining the dangerous conditions that health and humanitarian workers face in many countries. These tragic events further underline the truly heroic and courageous efforts of the frontline health workers, often working under very dangerous conditions, all in efforts to protect children from lifelong polio-paralysis.

Afghanistan
- One new WPV case was reported in the past week (WPV1 from Hilmand), bringing the total number of WPV cases for 2012 to 34. It is the most recent case in the country, and had onset of paralysis on [19 Nov 2012].
- The Inter-Ministerial Task Force held its 1st meeting on [11 Dec 2012] chaired by the deputy minister and co-chaired by focal person for polio eradication.
- Preparations are ongoing for the December Subnational Immunization Days (SNIDs), to be conducted in 14 high-risk districts and some border districts from [16-19 Dec 2012].
- OPV (oral polio vaccine) was administered as part of a measles campaign began in 18 provinces, which began on [1 Dec 2012].

Nigeria
- 7 new WPV cases were reported in the past week (2 cases of WPV1 from Katsina, 1 WPV1 from Kaduna, 1 WPV1 from Kano, 1 WPV1 from FCT, 1 WPV3 from Taraba, and 1 WPV3 from Yobe), bringing the total number of WPV cases for 2012 to 118. The WPV1 from Kaduna is the most recent in the country and had onset of paralysis on [17 Nov 2012].
- The 2 new WPV3 cases reported are particularly concerning, as Nigeria is now the only country in the world reporting cases due to this strain over the past 6 months. Taraba's previous WPV3 case dates back to July [2012], and a comprehensive outbreak response is urgently needed.
- Trivalent OPV was added to Child Health Days (with meningitis vaccine) from [1-10 Dec 2012], and subnational Immunization Plus Days (IPDs) will be conducted using bivalent OPV (15-18 Dec 2012). This will be an opportunity to administer 2 additional doses of OPV to children in highest-risk areas, within the space of a single month.

Pakistan
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recently reported WPV case occurred in Federally Administered Tribal Areas (WPV1) with onset of paralysis on [10 Nov 2012]. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 56.
- However, 2 new circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases were reported in the past week from Killa Abdullah in Balochistan, bringing the total number of cVDPV2 cases to 12 (all from the greater Quetta area of Balochistan).
- Response vaccination activities began in all Union-Councils of the Killa Abdullah district this week. Trivalent OPV was used for all union councils except for one team in Boghra that used bivalent OPV. After this campaign is concluded, the micro-plan for Killa Abdullah will be updated.
- An All Political Parties Conference was held in Killa Abdullah on [6 Dec 2012] to sustain the support of all political parties for polio eradication campaigns in the district. The conference provided an opportunity to share the current situation of polio eradication in the district, dispel misconceptions regarding immunization and encourage the parties to actively participate in the upcoming campaigns. Members of 9 political parties participated in the event.
- Preparations for SNIDs scheduled for [17-19 Dec 2012] are underway.
- The Polio Eradication Technical Advisory Group meeting is scheduled for [14-15 Dec 2012] in Islamabad.

Angola
- No new cases were reported in the past week. No cases have been reported in 2012. The country reported a total of 5 cases in 2011, and the last case had onset of paralysis on [7 Jul 2011] in Uige in the country's north.
- SNIDs with trivalent OPV were conducted on [7-10 Dec 2012].

Chad
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The most recently reported WPV case occurred in the Lac region (WPV1) with onset of paralysis on [14 Jun 2012]. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 5.
- One new cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week, bringing the total number of cVDPV2 cases to 12.
- Staggered SNIDs were conducted on [23-25 Nov 2012] in the south and east and were conducted on [9-11 Dec 2012] in the north and west, using trivalent OPV. Staggering activities allows the redeployment of all available technical staff to support the activity in various areas.
- Efforts are ongoing to strengthen subnational surveillance sensitivity, with trainings of health centers staff in key areas being conducted.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. No WPV cases have been reported in 2012. The total number of WPV cases for 2011 is 93 (all WPV1). The most recent case had onset of paralysis on [20 Dec 2011] in Maniema province.
- Although the country has not reported a WPV case since December 2011, it has been affected by a cVDPV2 outbreak in Katanga province in 2012, with 17 cases reported (most recent case: (4 Apr 2012). Efforts are focused on ensuring the cVDPV2 outbreak is fully stopped.
- Following recent insecurity, most UN staff has now returned to Goma. However, the security situation continues to be evaluated.
- A polio campaign for 27 Nov 2012 was postponed in North Kivu. OPV is also being added to measles campaigns and other humanitarian interventions planned in internally-displaced persons (IDPs) camps.

Horn of Africa
- Efforts are continuing to stop an ongoing cVDPV2 outbreak in Kenya and parts of Somalia (in a Somali refugee camp in Dadaab, Kenya, and Kismayo, south-central Somalia).
- Immunizations of older age groups have taken place in Dadaab. In Somalia, campaigns have been conducted in border areas with Kenya and Ethiopia, and in some areas of central Somalia (access allowing).
- Across the region, OPV continues to be added to broader humanitarian response activities.
- New tactics are being explored to further boost immunity levels in and around inaccessible areas of south-central Somalia. Potential activities include focusing on people in transit to/from inaccessible areas, using local negotiators to allow safe passage of vaccination teams to inaccessible areas, and immunizing populations bordering inaccessible areas.

West Africa
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. No WPV cases have been reported in 2012. The total number of WPV cases for 2011 in West Africa remains 51 (36 from Cote d'Ivoire, 3 from Guinea, 7 from Mali, and 5 from Niger). The most recent case from the region (WPV1 from Niger) had onset of paralysis on [22 Dec 2011].
- SIAs in Benin with Vitamin A and deworming tablets were conducted from [7-9 Dec 2012].
- OPV continues to be added to broader humanitarian response activities across the region.

